  "issue_number": 1756,
  "issue_title": "Conjuring a permanent onto the battlefield fires no enters-the-battlefield triggers and grants no summoning sickness (CR 603.6a / CR 302.6)",
  "issue_body": "## Summary\n\n`Effect::Conjure` puts a card from outside the game directly onto the battlefield, but it bypasses the normal battlefield-entry pipeline. In `crates/engine/src/game/effects/conjure.rs`, the resolver creates the object with `zones::create_object` and then emits **only** a bespoke `GameEvent::ObjectConjured`:\n\n```rust\n// crates/engine/src/game/effects/conjure.rs (before fix)\nlet obj_id = zones::create_object(state, CardId(0), ability.controller, conjure_card.name.clone(), destination);\n// ... apply card face, set tapped ...\nif destination == Zone::Battlefield {\n    crate::game::restrictions::record_battlefield_entry(state, obj_id);\n    crate::game::layers::mark_layers_entered(state, obj_id);\n}\nevents.push(GameEvent::ObjectConjured { object_id: obj_id, name: conjure_card.name.clone() });\n```\n\nTwo things that every other battlefield entry does are missing:\n\n1. **No `GameEvent::ZoneChanged { from: None, to: Battlefield }` is emitted.** `zones::create_object` deliberately does not emit `ZoneChanged`, and the conjure resolver never does either. The ETB trigger matcher (`trigger_matchers.rs::match_changes_zone`) fires only on `GameEvent::ZoneChanged`; `ObjectConjured` is routed to the no-match branch. So **no enters-the-battlefield triggered ability ever fires** for a conjured permanent.\n2. **No `reset_for_battlefield_entry` call.** `create_object` does not set summoning sickness, and the conjure resolver doesn't either, so a conjured creature has **no summoning sickness** and could attack or pay `{T}` costs the turn it appears (CR 302.6).\n\nThe token resolver (`effects/token.rs`) gets this right: it calls `obj.reset_for_battlefield_entry(...)` and emits `ZoneChanged { from: None, to: Battlefield }` precisely \"so every ETB trigger matcher fires for tokens through the same code path used for normal battlefield entry.\" Conjure is the outlier.\n\n## Failure mode (concrete example)\n\n**Verdant Dread** (Alchemy) has a triggered ability \u2014 \"Whenever this Verdant Dread or another Verdant Dread you control enters, manifest dread\" \u2014 and an activated ability that **conjures a Verdant Dread onto the battlefield**.\n\n- Correct (CR 603.6a): when the activated ability resolves and the new Verdant Dread enters, the existing Verdant Dread's \"another Verdant Dread enters\" ability triggers (manifest dread), and the newcomer's own copy of the trigger checks the same event.\n- Current engine: the conjured Verdant Dread enters silently (only `ObjectConjured` is emitted), so **no manifest-dread trigger fires at all**.\n\nDownstream effects:\n\n- Every ETB triggered ability is skipped for conjured permanents \u2014 not just the conjuring card's own triggers, but board-wide watchers like **Soul Warden**, **Elesh Norn**, **Panharmonicon**-style doublers, and \"whenever a creature enters\" payoffs.\n- A conjured creature has no summoning sickness, so it can attack or crew/tap the turn it is conjured \u2014 an illegal action under CR 302.6.\n\nThis is analogous to how token creation is handled: tokens \"are zone changes from outside the game\" and emit `ZoneChanged { from: None, to: Battlefield }`; conjured battlefield permanents must do the same.\n\n## Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Resolve an `Effect::Conjure { destination: Zone::Battlefield, .. }` (e.g. Verdant Dread's activated ability) while a permanent with an ETB trigger (the conjuring card itself, or a Soul Warden) is on the battlefield.\n2. Observe that no `ZoneChanged` event is produced for the conjured object and no ETB ability triggers.\n3. Conjure a creature and observe it has no summoning sickness (it can attack the same turn).\n\n## Expected behavior\n\nA conjured permanent entering the battlefield emits `ZoneChanged { from: None, to: Battlefield }` so all enters-the-battlefield triggered abilities fire (CR 603.6a), and runs the standard entry reset so it has summoning sickness like any other new permanent (CR 302.6).\n\n## Actual behavior\n\nConjured battlefield permanents enter silently: no `ZoneChanged`, no ETB triggers, and no summoning sickness.\n\n## Suggested fix\n\nIn `conjure.rs`, for `destination == Zone::Battlefield`, mirror the token-entry path:\n\n- Call `obj.reset_for_battlefield_entry(state.turn_number)` before applying the `tapped` state (single authority for summoning sickness and per-turn entry flags).\n- After the object is finalized (and after `record_battlefield_entry` / `mark_layers_entered`), build a `snapshot_for_zone_change(obj_id, None, Zone::Battlefield)` record and push `GameEvent::ZoneChanged { object_id, from: None, to: Zone::Battlefield, record }` in addition to the existing `ObjectConjured` event (kept for animation/logging consumers).\n\nThis routes conjured battlefield entries through the same ETB matcher path as normal entries and token creation. (Non-battlefield conjure destinations are out of scope for CR 603.6a and keep their current behavior. Richer entry-replacement specs beyond `tapped` are a separate parser-level concern.)",
